---
description: Render best practices for render.yaml Blueprints and deployed services
alwaysApply: true
---

render-yaml-standards:

- Use `plan: free` unless the user specifies a paid plan.
- Mark secret environment variables with `sync: false` so users fill them in the Dashboard.
- Bind HTTP servers to `0.0.0.0:$PORT` — Render sets the `PORT` variable automatically.
- Choose the correct service type: `web` for public HTTP, `worker` for background jobs, `cron` for scheduled tasks, `static` for CDN-served sites, `pserv` for internal services.
- Use native runtimes (`node`, `python`, `go`, `rust`, `ruby`, `elixir`) when possible; fall back to `docker` only when needed.
- Wire databases with `fromDatabase` references instead of hard-coding connection strings.
- Keep one `render.yaml` at the repository root. For monorepos, set `rootDir` on each service.
- Include `buildCommand` and `startCommand` for every non-static service.
- Set `healthCheckPath` on web services so Render can verify readiness.
